FOODBORNE ILLNESS - UKRAINE: (LVIV) SMOKED FISH, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 25 Sep 2017, 9:33 PM
Source: Xinhua Net [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-09/25/c_136637503.htm


At least 56 people, including 4 children, were sickened by food poisoning in Ukraine's western city of Lviv, local authorities said on [Mon 25 Sep 2017]. A total of 4 people have received medical care at home, while 52 others have been hospitalized, said Lviv regional administration in a statement.

A person remains in critical condition in intensive care and 13 are in serious condition, while the rest are in stable condition, the statement added. All victims were diagnosed with an acute enteric infection. They fell ill after eating smoked fish purchased in a local market.

